summary:
There is no evidence linking elevated blood pH to stimulated protein synthesis in dialysis patients; instead, metabolic acidosis promotes protein breakdown through mechanisms like reduced enzyme function and systemic inflammation. The absence of studies showing beneficial effects from alkalinization—combined with established data demonstrating worsened outcomes during acidic states—supports concluding that higher pH does not enhance protein production. 

